tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: All measured values are within or close to normal ranges, except for mildly decreased HbA1c and creatinine. Low HbA1c may reflect recent changes in glucose metabolism or conditions affecting red cell turnover; low creatinine is likely not clinically significant in an elderly male with normal urea. No acute abnormalities detected. Correlate with clinical context if symptoms are present.
